sorry for the late turn around. 
I am not sure if you can join w/ hudi table from within a transformer. from what I know, incoming df is treated as a table (sparksession.registerTempTable()) and then you can perform a sql query on top of it to produce output df before ingesting to hudi. 

@bvaradar : Can you help here.

> @umehrot2 Thanks for the additional fix!
> One thing I noticed is that the `DataSourceWriteOptions.KEYGENERATOR_CLASS` has a default value but `HoodieWriteConfig.KEYGENERATOR_CLASS` doesn't. I think we should have the same default values at both places if it's not intentional.

@codope good catch. I checked the history, and seems like it was done intentionally https://github.com/apache/hudi/pull/2993#discussion_r642188609 . @nsivabalan can confirm since he reviewed it.

@nsivabalan  Thanks! Yes it worked after using this property while writing the data.
I am running into a different issue which says java.lang.RuntimeException: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: Class "org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.HiveInputFormat" not found. I am assuming that is because I am running on Hive version 1.2.
Can you please confirm?
